I didn't like the sour cream in this pie, I tried it again without it and I liked it a lot better. Texture-wise it wasn't totally necessary, it actually held together better, or at least mine did. I liked the nuttiness of the streusel, so I almost doubled it (about 1 1/2) the second time and everyone really liked the results. This is a very easy pie, great for beginners.

