Rating: 3
This apple pie is delicious - I love the crumbled topping. I've already made it once, and plan again to make it tonight to bring to a Christmas Party. I did not go with their pastry, I prefer the Flaky Pastry Crust recipe in "The Joy of Cooking". Only one change would I make to the above recipe: double the amount of streusel topping and keep the amount of apples to a minimum for maximum surface area for the streusel.

Rating: 3
Interesting taste and very good. Make sure you use fine cornmeal. Cut down on the cloves.(too overwhelming). Changes I made to the filling: use only a pinch of cloves, 1/8 teaspoon fresh nutmeg, 1/8 cup white sugar and 1/8 cup packed light brown sugar in place of the 1/4 cup white sugar. I think the pie tasted great the second day. It is an interesting tasting pie with the cornmeal struesel on top.

